# ============================================================
# .gitignore — Migrant Networks and International Trade
# ============================================================
# Strategy: commit code + raw Destatis inputs + final tables/figures.
# Exclude regenerable intermediate objects, the large CEPII file,
# personal documents, third-party copyrighted material, and OS/editor junk.

# --- Tooling / local config ---
.claude/

# --- OS / editor junk ---
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
~$*
*.tmp
.Rhistory
.Rapp.history
**/.Rapp.history
.RData
.Rproj.user/

# --- Generated intermediate objects (regenerate via the pipeline) ---
# Final tables/figures are kept as .tex/.csv/.png; the .rds copies are not needed.
data/*.rds

# --- Large raw data (the full file is NOT committed) ---
# Full CEPII Gravity database (~1.2 GB). The repo instead ships a tiny
# Germany-origin subset (data/cepii_gravity_germany_subset.csv, committed),
# which is all the pipeline uses. Keep the full download out of the repo.
data/Gravity_V202211.csv

# --- Personal documents (not part of the project) ---
Chinamere_CV_EN.docx
Chinamere_Lebenslauf_DE.docx
# Presentation slides — embed campus email in metadata + 37 speaker-note pages
Chinamere_Migrant_Networks_and_International_Trade.pptx

# --- Third-party / copyrighted material (do not redistribute) ---
1-s2.0-*.pdf
Final_Paper_*.pdf
The Economic Journal*.pdf
orefice_et_al_*.pdf
ecoj*.pdf
consequences_migration_*.pdf
# Review of Economics & Statistics article (copyrighted)
data/rest_a_01165.pdf
# Eurostat news release (third-party)
data/3-04032016-AP-EN.pdf
# seminar assignment brief (instructor material, not needed for replication)
assignment_chinamere_trade.pdf

# --- Working drafts / notes (not needed for replication) ---
draft2.docx
notes.docx
notes.pdf
